Function AddElement(array, element):
    If array is full:
        Create a new array with double the size
        Copy elements from the old array to the new array
    Add the element to the next available position in the array
    Return the updated array

Function DeleteElement(array, index):
    If index is valid:
        For each element from index to the end of the array:
            Shift the element one position to the left
        Reduce the size of the array by 1
    Else:
        Print "Invalid index"
    Return the updated array
